name: citrate (Si)-synthase
classes: Acyl groups converted into alkyl groups on transfer
comment: The stereospecificity of this enzyme is opposite to that of EC 2.3.3.3, citrate (Re)-synthase, which is found in some anaerobes. Citrate synthase for which the stereospecificity with respect to C2 of oxaloacetate has not been established are included in EC 2.3.3.16, citrate synthase.

references.title: Stereochemistry of si-citrate synthase and ATP-citrate-lyase reactions.

Identification of the stereoisomeric configurations of methylcitric acid produced by si-citrate synthase and methylcitrate synthase using capillary gas chromatography-mass spectrometry.
